{
  "texts": [
    "The peer review network structure dictated which reviewers evaluated which artifacts.",
    "Each assessment depended on both the artifact's quality and the reviewer's competence.",
    "Rashid et al. (2021) analyzed rubrics to see what features enhanced the writing of quality reviews.",
    "Measurement integrity as a desideratum for peer prediction was considered by Burrell and Schoenbeck (2021).",
    "(Peer prediction, or information elicitation without verification, is a paradigm for designing mechanisms that elicit reports about questions or tasks in settings where ground truth-and therefore the possibility of spot-checkingneed not exist)."
  ]
}